  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "##### $F_X(x)$: Función de probabilidad Acumulada en R:\n",
    "+ `q` es el vector de cuantiles (*quantiles*) con los valores de la variable aleatoria\n",
    "+ `pnorm(q, mean = , sd = )` nos da los valores de la función densidad de probabilidad con $\\mu = $ `mean` y $\\sigma = $ `sd` "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Fx <- pnorm(q = x, mean = 0, sd = 1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 65,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "skip"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "gFx <- ggplot() + \n",
    "  geom_line(aes(x = x, y = Fx), size = 1.25, show.legend = F) + \n",
    "  ylab(\"F(x)\") +\n",
    "  xlab(\"x\") +\n",
    "  ggtitle(\"Función Probabilidad Acumulada - Distribución Normal\") + \n",
    "  scale_y_continuous(expand=c(0,0), limits = c(-0.01,1.01)) + \n",
    "  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(-3,-2,-1,0,1,2,3),\n",
    "                     labels = c(expression(paste(mu,\"-3\",sigma)),\n",
    "                                expression(paste(mu, \"-2\",sigma)),\n",
    "                                expression(paste(mu, \"- \",sigma)),\n",
    "                                expression(paste(mu)),\n",
    "                                expression(paste(mu, \"+\",sigma)),\n",
    "                                expression(paste(mu, \"+2\",sigma)),\n",
    "                                expression(paste(mu, \"+3\",sigma))),\n",
    "                     limits = c(-4,4), expand=c(0,0))+\n",
    "temajuan3 "
   ]
  },
