  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "La media muestral no le pega a la media...como suele pasar."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "pero ahora sacamos 10000 medias, cada una con $n=6$ elementos. Y vemos el histograma."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 180,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mmv <- vector(mode = \"numeric\", length = 10000)\n",
    "for(i in 1:10000){mmv[i] <- mean(runif(n = 6, min = 4, max = 6))}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 183,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "skip"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mi = 5; s = sqrt(3)/(3*sqrt(6));\n",
    "x = seq(mi-3*s, mi+3*s, 0.01); y <- dnorm(x = x, mean = mi, sd = s)\n",
    "ghm <- ggplot() +   geom_histogram(aes(x = mmv, y = ..density..),colour = \"Deepskyblue4\", fill = \"Deepskyblue4\",alpha = 0.3, bins = nclass.FD(an))  +\n",
    "geom_line(aes(x = x, y = y)) +   \n",
    "geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mm), colour = \"red3\", lwd = 1, lty = 2)+\n",
    "xlab(TeX(\"$\\\\bar{X} = \\\\sum_{i = 1}{n = 6} \\\\frac{X_i}{6}$\")) + ylab(\"Densidad de Probabilidad\") + ggtitle(\"Medias muestrales de una Distribución Unifrome....distribuídas normalmente :)\") +   temajuan3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 184,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
